name: Josh Allen
summary: Buffalo Bills' quarterback Josh Allen has been cleared to play against the Miami Dolphins on Thursday Night Football. Allen, who injured his non-throwing hand last week against the Arizona Cardinals, said that his hand is "good, ready to go" for the short week. Allen threw for 2 touchdowns and ran for 2 others in the Bills' 34-28 win over the Cardinals. Cornerback Taron Johnson, however, has been ruled out for the game against the Dolphins with a concussion. Allen's return is a major boost for the Bills, who are looking to extend their winning streak to three games. The Dolphins, meanwhile, are looking to snap a two-game losing streak and improve their playoff chances.

name: Pepsi
summary: PepsiCo is expanding its offerings with DRIPS By PEPSI™, a mixology line of crafted beverages. New York City will be the first to experience DRIPS this month. In a promotional campaign, Pepsi delivery cars are chasing pizza in partnership with DoorDash. Pepsi is also featured in several entertainment news articles. Judd Apatow and Steven Spielberg are collaborating on a film about the Coke vs. Pepsi rivalry titled "Cola Wars." Additionally, a discontinued Pepsi rival, Big Red, is reportedly making a comeback to challenge Coca-Cola. Pepsi has also released a new NFL commercial featuring Travis Kelce, Josh Allen, and Megan Thee Stallion. Statistical data on advertising spending by beverage brands in the US further highlights Pepsi's presence in the market.

name: Shohei Ohtani
summary: Shohei Ohtani, a star for the Los Angeles Dodgers, is making history in Major League Baseball. He is closing in on becoming the first player to hit 50 home runs and steal 50 bases in the same season (known as the "50-50 club"). Ohtani's remarkable performance includes a recent 450-foot home run, bringing his total to 46, and a 48th stolen base. Experts have discussed the significance of Ohtani's pursuit of the 50-50 milestone, noting that it is a rare feat in baseball history. Some have even suggested that Ohtani could potentially pitch out of the bullpen in the playoffs, showcasing his versatility as both a hitter and a pitcher. With his impressive stats and the support of his team, Ohtani is on track to make baseball history and solidify his status as one of the greatest players in the sport.

name: Edward Caban
summary: The New York Police Department (NYPD) has been embroiled in a series of scandals and investigations. Mayor Eric Adams has declined to comment on his support for embattled Police Commissioner Edward Caban. Caban has since resigned, followed by federal investigators seizing phones from him and four other top mayoral deputies. The investigation focuses on alleged misconduct and potential corruption within the NYPD. Questions have also been raised about Caban's twin brother, a former cop with a checkered past, who is reportedly being investigated as a potential "fixer" for crime hotspots in the city. Amid the investigations, the NYPD has been accused of dismissing hundreds of misconduct cases without proper review. These revelations have cast a shadow over the NYPD and its leadership, fueling scrutiny and speculation about the extent of wrongdoing within the department.

summary: Cardi B and her husband, Offset, have welcomed their third child together, a baby girl. The news comes just weeks after Cardi B filed for divorce from Offset. The couple has been married since 2017 and has two other children together, a daughter named Kulture Kiari Cephus and a son named Wave Set Cephus. Cardi B announced the birth of her third child with a photo of the baby's feet and a caption that read, "The prettiest lil thing." The couple has not yet announced the name of their new child.

name: Field of Dreams
summary: Recent news headlines have focused on the passing of renowned actor James Earl Jones, known for his iconic voice in "Star Wars" and his memorable speech in "Field of Dreams." Mourning fans have taken to online platforms to share their condolences, while tributes from fellow actors like Kevin Costner have highlighted Jones' unique talent and charisma. Meanwhile, an exclusive report reveals the sale of the "Field of Dreams" movie site to a local nonprofit organization, ensuring its preservation for future generations. Additionally, articles have explored the profound impact of Jones' voice, not only in cinema but also in baseball and beyond, marking the passage of time and inspiring hope. Lastly, a special opportunity for AARP members is being offered to watch "Field of Dreams" for free, making it possible for fans to revisit and appreciate Jones' unforgettable performance.
